# 1. ランニング中の出会い

Tsukasa: Huff... Huff...
Tsukasa: A clear blue sky... What a beautifully sunny day! I couldn't have asked for better running conditions!
Tsukasa: I need to keep building up my stamina in order to get the most out of my training at Morinomiya.
Tsukasa: (I had quite a lot of confidence in my endurance, but I still pale in comparison to the boys enrolled there.)
Tsukasa: (I have to keep trying, and build the proficiency to properly play any role I am given.)
Tsukasa: Alright, I'll finish this leg and keep going all out during my next exercise...!
???: <Let's go, Tsukasa! You can do it, Tsukasa♪>
Tsukasa: Hm?
Tsukasa: Ah, if it isn't Miku! What brings you here?
Miku: <So, the others and I are spending today cheering on everyone from Wonderlands×Showtime♪>
Miku: <We know you guys all work really hard studying and practicing during your days off, so we're gonna give you lots of support☆>
Miku: <So! Let's go, Tsukasa♪>
Tsukasa: Hah hah hah! Now I understand. Thank you, Miku. I'm feeling more motivated already!
Miku: <Really?!>
Tsukasa: Yes! I was actually just about to wrap up my run, but I'm thinking about doing an extra lap now...
???: M-Meow...
Tsukasa: Hm...?
Miku: <Oh, Tsukasa, did you hear that just now?!>
Tsukasa: You heard it as well? What do you think it—
???: Meowww...
Miku: <There it is again! It sounds like...>
Tsukasa: Yes, a cat... But it doesn't sound all that well...
Tsukasa: What if it's in trouble...? We need to find it!
Miku: <Right! Let's see... I think it might be over there!>
Tsukasa: Alright, let's go!
Tsukasa: This seems like the right spot...
Miku: <Tsukasa! Tsukasa! Look at the pond over there!>
Cat: Meow...
Tsukasa: Oh no... He's gotten himself stuck on one of the stepping stones...!
Miku: <He looks so scared... Please, Tsukasa, you gotta save him!>
Tsukasa: That's the plan! I just need to find a place where I can jump close enough to him...
Tsukasa: (No, I'm not seeing any good spots. And the stone he's on is too small for me to jump to directly. I'd surely scare him if I were to slip and fall in...)
Tsukasa: (Isn't there any other way...?)
Miku: <I know! What if you showed him what to do?>
Tsukasa: Showed him?
Miku: <Yeah! You can show him what he's gotta do to get back to land safely!>
Miku: <KAITO and the others model stuff for me all the time when we're practicing☆>
Tsukasa: I see. That may be worth a try...
Tsukasa: I don't know if I'll succeed... But I may be able to help him if I put my acting skills on full display!
Tsukasa: You there, cat!
Cat: ...?
Tsukasa: Listen up. Watch what I'm about to do. You need to jump! Like...!
Tsukasa: This!!!!
Cat: ...?
Miku: <He's tilting his head...>
Tsukasa: He looks confused...
Tsukasa: But he might understand if I keep trying. So, let me try that again!
Tsukasa: Watch. Plant your legs like this, make sure you have a good footing...
Tsukasa: And jump! Like this...!
Cat: Meow...
Tsukasa: Don't worry! You can do it...!
Cat: Me-Meow...!
Miku: <Oh, I think he's trying to jump now!>
Tsukasa: Yes, that's it! We can try jumping together!
Tsukasa: Ready?! One, two...!!
Tsukasa: Three!!!
Cat: Meow...!!
Tsukasa: You...
Tsukasa: You did it!!
Miku: <That was amazing! It was so cool how you flew up and stuck the landing☆>
Tsukasa: Yes, that was a wonderful display of courage! Umm...
Tsukasa: Nyantaro!!
Cat: Meow!
Miku: <Oh, his name is Nyantaro☆>
Miku: <Hehe. I'm so glad that you're smiling now, Nyantaro♪>
Tsukasa: Actually, I just decided to name him that...
Tsukasa: Hm? What's this shape on your back...?
Tsukasa: It's a star! I couldn't tell earlier since you were too far away... That's incredible, Nyantaro!
Cat: Meow...
Tsukasa: Hey, wait...!
Miku: <There he goes...>
Tsukasa: Well, he lost interest rather quickly...
Tsukasa: However, as short as that interaction was, we became friends by accomplishing something together. Let us wish him the best in life!
Tsukasa: Be strong, Nyantaro!
Miku: <Bye bye!>
Cat: Meow...!
Miku: <Hehe. He replied back♪>
Tsukasa: Yes, and he sounded incredibly happy!
Tsukasa: Anyway, now that Nyantaro is safely back on dry land, we should get back to what we were doing!
Miku: <Right! I'm gonna cheer you on like crazy☆>
Airi: This way, Mizuki! I'm starting to see the Ferris wheel!
Airi: The gondolas are supposed to be really cute, but we still can't see them very well from this far... We gotta get closer...!
Mizuki: You're walking so fast, Airi! Also, you seem way too excited today!
Airi: Of course I'm excited! I mean, today...
Airi: We get to visit a cat-themed carnival!
Airi: Just the thought of going to a carnival is fun, but this one's all about cats...! It's like a dream come true for me, you know?
Airi: From what we saw on social media, the Ferris wheel and all their other attractions have cats all over them. Which means...
Airi: It's guaranteed to be adorable...!!!
Mizuki: I see what you mean! And I know just how much you love cats, Airi.
Airi: Exactly! As much as I want to pet or hold real ones, I can't...
Airi: That's why I absolutely have to check out this carnival. I'll get to be around cats with none of the health risks, so it's going to be like paradise...!
Mizuki: Hehe. Then, let's have as much fun as we can today♪
Airi: Yeah! The carnival should be just through this park...
???: Heeeeeeey!!!
???: Nyantarooooooo!!!!! Where are yoooou?!
Mizuki: That sounds like...
